      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-bootstrap-llm"
        },
        "markdown": "## Example first graph request\\n\\nAfter the handshake, ask for a tiny declaration-first graph. For example:\\n\\n```text\\nNow create a very small Twilite graph in the current session.\\nAdd a declaration node, a reader port exposed by the declaration, one markdown node, and one reference edge.\\nKeep it minimal and valid.\\n```\\n\\nThe important part is the order: declaration first, then the exposed reader surface, then the content.",
        "_placement": {
          "version": 1,
          "state": "manually-shaped",
          "source": "manual",
          "updatedAt": 1781130437248,
          "reason": "node-drag"
        }
      }
    },
